messages.message: when you copy file A to a folder with another file with the same name, is it supposed to be that file A isn’t copied to that folder? I still get the popup `Successfully copied files. Click here to view`. on uat.dogfood
it didn’t get overwritten. i was expecting the file to be copied but renamed to `refiner(1).prog` . i’m not sure if thats expected behavior or if it should just not copy

Don’t quite remember if that’s the expected behaviour. I think @Jessica might have a better idea of what flags (if any) the copy API is being called with from the front end.  @achao might also remember.
